# IconProvider (Momentum) — Momentum guidance (Cursor)

**IconProvider** loads **Momentum icons** once at app shell using **`registerMomentumIcons`** from **`@momentum-design/icons/dist/esm/svg`** so **`Icon`**/`IconNames` resolve **`name`** strings.

See also: [Icon](./icon.mdc).

Browse the [Momentum Components catalog](https://momentum.design/en/components/) for naming; Storybook documents props and examples. Reference: [Storybook — IconProvider / Docs](https://momentum.design/storybook-static/index.html?path=/docs/components-iconprovider-iconprovider--docs).

---

## Import

Requires <ThemeProvider> ancestor. See setup.mdc.

```jsx
import { IconProvider } from "@momentum-design/components/dist/react";
import { registerMomentumIcons } from "@momentum-design/icons/dist/esm/svg";
```

---

## What it is

- **`IconProvider`** wraps the subtree that renders **`Icon`** (often **`ThemeProvider`** → **`IconProvider`** → app).  
- **`registerMomentumIcons`** imports registry modules **once**—avoid duplicate registration across bundles.  
- Unknown **`Icon`** **`name`** logs a warning and renders nothing—verify **`name`** against **`IconNames`** / Storybook.

---

## Example — shell wiring

```jsx
import { ThemeProvider, IconProvider } from "@momentum-design/components/dist/react";
import { registerMomentumIcons } from "@momentum-design/icons/dist/esm/svg";

registerMomentumIcons();

export function AppShell({ children }) {
  return (
    <ThemeProvider theme="light">
      <IconProvider>{children}</IconProvider>
    </ThemeProvider>
  );
}
```

---

## Checklist for Cursor prototypes

- [ ] Call **`registerMomentumIcons`** **once** before **`Icon`** renders  
- [ ] **`ThemeProvider`** **outside** **`IconProvider`** per [setup.mdc](../setup.mdc)  
- [ ] Icon **`name`** strings align with **`IconNames`** / Storybook  

Cross-check [Storybook — IconProvider / Docs](https://momentum.design/storybook-static/index.html?path=/docs/components-iconprovider-iconprovider--docs) and your installed package version.
